{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0478c3ad-acc4-42a8-bb10-de6a7e5e8282","content":"The template is **functional but not fully ready** for NuGet publishing. Here's what's missing:\n\n| Field | Status |\n|-------|--------|\n| `$schema` | ❌ Missing — add for validation support |\n| `identity` | ✅ |\n| `name` | ✅ |\n| `shortName` | ✅ |\n| `author` | ✅ |\n| `classifications` | ✅ |\n| `tags` | ✅ |\n| `description` | ❌ Missing — critical for NuGet discoverability |\n| `groupIdentity` | ❌ Missing — recommended for grouping related templates |\n\n**Key recommendations:**\n\n1. **Add `description`** — without it, users searching NuGet won't know what the template does.\n2. **Add `$schema`** — `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` enables editor validation.\n3. **Add `groupIdentity`** (e.g., `\"MyCompany.WebApi\"`) — needed if you plan to ship multiple variants.\n\nAlso ensure you have a `.csproj` or `.nuspec` with proper NuGet package metadata (`PackageId`, `Version`, `PackageType` set to `Template`, etc.) — the template.json alone isn't enough to produce a publishable package.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b11383e4-cc03-4502-8cf6-54aba1db58f9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check against the required and recommended fields for .NET template packages.\n\nRequired fields for template.json:\n- `$schema` - Missing! Should reference the template schema\n- `identity` - ✅ Present\n- `name` - ✅ Present\n- `shortName` - ✅ Present\n- `author` - ✅ Present\n- `classifications` - ✅ Present\n- `tags` - ✅ Present with language and type\n\nMissing/Issues:\n1. **`$schema`** - Not present. While not strictly required for functionality, it's best practice for validation.\n\n\n2. **`groupIdentity`** - Missing. Recommended for NuGet publishing to group related templates.\n3. **`precedence`** - Missing. Useful when multiple versions of a template exist.\n4. **`description`** - Missing! This is important for discoverability on NuGet.\n5. **`defaultName`** - Missing. Not required but useful for setting default project names.\n\nThe template is functional but has some gaps for NuGet publishing—notably the missing `description` field which affects discoverability, plus `$schema` for validation. I should also check if you need a `.nuspec` file or other packaging configuration for the NuGet publish process.","outputTokens":681,"requestId":"D006:11A664:11CCDAC:142C258:69F94148"},"id":"ee9fef32-8a97-4dd6-8037-3a7e9b1048dd","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:01:11.455Z","parentId":"09294b5a-ab10-49d2-be38-325d839f747f"}
